observations.reason:
Some purchases were still made through reimbursements.
1. All procurement should be in accordance with the approved APP. Make sure that the APP were carefully planned and scheduled to better manage the resources, produce economical result, make the procurement procedures more efficient and practical in the part of the government and do away with redundancy;
2. The HOPE (Municipal Mayor) should issue an Executive Order reconstituting the membership of the BAC including its Secretariat and prescribing their duties and functions pursuant to RA 9184 and its IRR every year;
3. In all instances of procurement, the BAC shall strictly adhere to the advertisement and posting requirements prescribed in Section 21 of RA 9184;
4. Strictly adhere to the guidelines prescribed in Annex H of IRR, RA 9184 for the alternative methods of procurement; and
5. Refrain from purchasing goods and services through reimbursements and that procurement of common use goods and equipment should be procured in the PS-DBM, if available or in bulk quantities, to avoid piecemeal purchases. Purchasing in bulk ultimately results to savings for the Municipality in terms of lower costs, less time and effort devoted to the process of procurement, inspection and acceptance, and corresponding disbursement.

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
terminate the contracts of the consultants whose services are only duplication of the functions of regular employees or whose works could be performed by existing plantilla personnel;
in case there is really a need for consultants, (a) engage only experts in their respective fields; (b) observe rules and regulations on the hiring of consultants as provided by IRR of RA No. 9184, COA Circular 2012-003 dated October 29, 2012 and DBM National Budget Circular No. 433 dated March 1, 1994. and (c) support payments for consultancy services with adequate documentation, otherwise a Notice of Suspension/Disallowance will be served; and amend the contracts of the consultants to properly match that of the needs of the LCE or any officials needing assistance thereof to eliminate the dubious nature of hiring said consultants.
